   "source": [
    "Probability: This is a measure of the chance that a certain event will occur out all possible events. It's usually presented as a ratio or fraction, and it ranges from 0 (meaning the event will not happen) to 1 (meaning the event is certain to happen).\n",
    "\n",
    "Likelihood: In statistical context, likelihood is a function that measures the plausibility of a particular parameter value given some observed data. It quanties how well a specific outcome supports specific parameter values.\n",
    "    \n",
    "More Definitions:\n",
    "A probability quantifies how often you observe a certain outcome of a test, given a certain understanding of the underlying data\n",
    "\n",
    "Alikelihood quantifies how good one's model is, given a set of data that's been observed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Probabilities describe test outcomes, while likelihoods describe models."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7c0d6b2b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "✅ Core Difference\n",
    "Aspect\tProbability\tLikelihood\n",
    "Meaning\tChance of data given parameters\tHow likely parameters are given data\n",
    "Notation\tP(Data∣θ)\tL(θ∣Data)\n",
    "Variable\tData varies\tParameters vary\n",
    "Known\tParameters are known\tData is known\n",
    "Used in\tPrediction\tParameter estimation\n",
    "🎯 Simple Intuition\n",
    "🔹 Probability\n",
    "\n",
    "“If I know the model, what data can I expect?”\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "If a coin is fair (θ = 0.5),\n",
    "👉 What is the probability of getting 3 heads in 5 tosses?\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Likelihood\n",
    "\n",
    "“Given the data, what model is most likely?”\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "You observed: H, H, T, H, H\n",
    "👉 What is the probability that the coin is biased?\n",
    "\n",
    "📌 Mathematical View\n",
    "\n",
    "For a coin toss:\n",
    "\n",
    "P(X∣θ)=θ\n",
    "x\n",
    "(1−θ)\n",
    "n−x\n",
    "\n",
    "Probability: Fix θ, vary X\n",
    "Likelihood: Fix X, vary θ\n",
    "🧠 In Machine Learning\n",
    "✅ Probability is used in:\n",
    "Predicting outputs\n",
    "Generative models\n",
    "Bayesian inference\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "P(y∣x) in classification\n",
    "✅ Likelihood is used in:\n",
    "Model training\n",
    "Parameter estimation\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Especially in Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE):\n",
    "\n",
    "Choose θ that maximizes likelihood\n",
    "🔥 Key Interview Line (Must Remember)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Probability: Data is random, parameters are fixed\n",
    "👉 Likelihood: Data is fixed, parameters are variable\n",
    "\n",
    "💡 Real ML Example\n",
    "In Logistic Regression:\n",
    "We model:\n",
    "P(y∣x,θ)\n",
    "During training:\n",
    "👉 We maximize likelihood to find best θ\n",
    "🚀 Quick Analogy\n",
    "Probability: “What will happen?”\n",
    "Likelihood: “What explains what already happened?”\n",
    "\n",
    "If you want, I can also explain:\n",
    "\n",
    "MLE vs MAP vs Bayesian inference\n",
    "Or give \n",
    "interview questions based on this concept (very commonly asked at companies like Accenture, KPMG, etc.)"
   ]
